	High brow low perks.	The hotel is nice and has quaint rooms. We stayed in one facing the park. I don't know if this is supposed to be the quiet side since the trolley cars and a busy street are right below. The view was lovely though. There are a lot of people standing around to serve you for a price. You can only valet park. The man who stands outside is very rude we weren't sure what his title was but he was very condescending to my husband. The valet parking attendants drive your vehicle like it's a drag race and every time you go to get your car you have to wait a long time for them to find it and tip them everytime. The desk clerk failed to tell us there is only coffee downstairs in the lobby from 5am to 7am and there aren't any coffee makers in the rooms, or microwaves, or refrigerators. It's just a room with a bed and shower no perks at all. If you want to order coffee from the kitchen it's over $13 with tip and a delivery fee as well so plan on going without unless you want to spend $20 for a cup of coffee. They also have to deliver your ice to you so if you want a cold drink plan on tipping for ice delivery. You also have to tip the door person, the bell hop, housekeeping if they bring an extra roll a way bed etc. I have no idea how much we ended up spending staying here but if we'd have stayed at a midlevel hotel I am sure we'd at least gotten a cup of coffee out of it!I won't be back to this hotel. I was very unsatisfied with the lack of amenities. How hard is it to include a coffee maker in a room? But then they couldn't make $20 per cup I guess.The pool and spa close at 9pm as well. We never even saw it since we went out to dinner in the city. That was one of the reasons we stayed here because our daughter likes to swim. Children aren't allowed at the pool only over 16 years old.	
