Apr 14 2009	Small highly-personalized luxury hotel	The Huntington is member of the &quot;Small Luxury Hotels&quot; - and it deserves it well. No name-tag bearing business guests, but style, classic charme and a highly-personalized service. And a breathtaking pool and spa area! One of the best 5-star hotel bets in San Francisco.Location: On top of Nob Hill, across Huntington Park. Short walking distance (or cable car) to Union Square and restaurants. Neighborhood and location can't be better.Building/public areas: Classic grandeur, with antiques and oil paintings in the lobby. San Francisco's best bar (very popular with locals).Rooms: We had a freshly renovated, mint-colored room which was spacious, with a two-room marble bathroom and all modern amenities.Pool and Spa: Just beautiful. The indoor pool could be a little larger, but it is just a wonderful area with great views, an outside terrace, a gas fireplace, complimentary beverages and fruit throughout the day, sauna, steam room.. everything you want.Service: We loved the Huntington's service. Everybody was most welcoming. We always had chats with the bell boys and they gave us good tips. Extra-wishes were easily satisfied.Dining: We had no chance to dine at the Big 4 restaurant, but breakfast was always excellent. And the bar. The bar! The bar!! Outstanding.Value: We got the room at an unbelievably good rate. Valet parking is convenient but expensive. If you want to save $7 per night, you can park your car by yourself in one of the two adjacent public garages. WiFi cost $9.95 per 24 hours.	
