Aug 28 2008 	Old Frisco's Finest Small Hotel	I was booked into this 1920s vintage hotel on Nob Hill for a business meeting. And frankly I had a terrific experience. The location is outstanding with cable car service literally just outside the front entrance. You can get just about anywhere in less than 10 minutes.The lobby is rather small in keeping with the original time period of construction. And the rooms generally are as well. I had what they referred to as a luxury suite on the 11th floor and it was rather large for a vintage hotel (see video of Room 1103).The bed had a firm mattress and not the soft type you find at most Hyatts, Hiltons &amp; Marriotts. But frankly it added to the charm of the stay. There is actually a still operational mail chute by the elevators.I propped open the window in my shower and enjoyed a splendid view to start the morning. I can't recall the last time I could make a statement like that regarding a shower and shave.The meeting rooms were rather tight but served their purposes for a meeting of 15.The bell staff were attentive and friendly. I could live without the $45 a day valet parking charge. But on Nob Hill it is to be expected.I would certainly enjoy a return visit with my wife at a future date.	
